document.title: CVS Pharmacy, Inc. Ibuprofen Tablets Drug Facts

list.item: •temporarily relieves minor aches and pains due to:

text.paragraph: Allergy alert: Ibuprofen may cause a severe allergic reaction, especially in people allergic to aspirin.
If an allergic reaction occurs, stop use and seek medical help right away.
Stomach bleeding warning: This product contains an NSAID, which may cause severe stomach bleeding. The chances are higher if you

list.item: •have had stomach ulcers or bleeding problems
•take a blood thinning (anticoagulant) or steroid drug
•take other drugs containing prescription or nonprescription NSAIDs [aspirin, ibuprofen, naproxen, or others]
•have 3 or more alcoholic drinks every day while using this product
•take more or for a longer time than directed

text.paragraph: Heart attack and stroke warning: NSAIDs, except aspirin, increase the risk of heart attack, heart failure, and stroke. These can be fatal. The risk is higher if you use more than directed or for longer than directed.

list.item: •if you have ever had an allergic reaction to ibuprofen or any other pain reliever/fever reducer

section.title: Ask a doctor before use if

list.item: •you have problems or serious side effects from taking pain relievers or fever reducers
•the stomach bleeding warning applies to you
•you have a history of stomach problems, such as heartburn
•you have high blood pressure, heart disease, liver cirrhosis, kidney disease, asthma, or had a stroke

section.title: Ask a doctor or pharmacist before use if you are

list.item: •taking aspirin for heart attack or stroke, because ibuprofen may decrease this benefit of aspirin
•under a doctor’s care for any serious condition
•take with food or milk if stomach upset occurs

section.title: Stop use and ask a doctor if

list.item: •you experience any of the following signs of stomach bleeding:
•have stomach pain that does not get better
•you have symptoms of heart problems or stroke:
•weakness in one part or side of body
•pain gets worse or lasts more than 10 days
•fever gets worse or lasts more than 3 days
•redness or swelling is present in the painful area

code.displayName: OTC - PREGNANCY OR BREAST FEEDING SECTION

text.paragraph: ask a health professional before use. It is especially important not to use ibuprofen during the last 3 months of pregnancy unless definitely directed to do so by a doctor because it may cause problems in the unborn child or complications during delivery.

code.displayName: OTC - KEEP OUT OF REACH OF CHILDREN SECTION

section.title: Keep out of reach of children.

text.paragraph: In case of overdose, get medical help or contact a Poison Control Center right away (1-800-222-1222).

list.item: •the smallest effective dose should be used
•take 1 tablet every 4 to 6 hours while symptoms persist
•if pain or fever does not respond to 1 tablet, 2 tablets may be used
•do not exceed 6 tablets in 24 hours, unless directed by a doctor
•read all warnings and directions before use
•avoid high humidity and excessive heat above 40°C (104°F)
